{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The article primarily addressed the issue of accuracy in common pedestrian detection, but it did not address some challenges, such as small-scale and occluded pedestrians.",
    "Reference [35] utilized the k-means clustering algorithm to extract initial pedestrian areas, employed RPN for rapid candidate region generation and proposed a cascaded multilevel feature fusion strategy to enhance the network's semantic information.",
    "They used the Online Hard Sample Mining (OHEM) method to train high-loss samples, which solved the imbalance between positive and negative samples and significantly improved the detection performance of the algorithm.",
    "Pedestrian detection has also been effective in the application of MASK R-CNN.Reference [36] based their framework on MASK R-CNN.",
    "They used Adam's improvement device to propose a small and small-scale RPN ratio, reducing the calculation redundancy."
  ],
